network.sh

Tool for measuring network throughput on a specified network interface. Used for
benchmarking wifi, ethernet, etc..

To run, start transferring data through the interface, then run this script. Pressing
^C will complete the test and calculate the average throughput.

Syntax:

./network.sh [ interface ] [ logfile ]

where: 
	interface is the interface to be benchmarked, e.g. eth0, wlan0, etc
	default is wlan0

	logfile is the name of the log. Default is the interface name with .log suffix,
	e.g. wlan0.log

